  "text": "Hemodynamic and echocardiographic characteristics of the groups are shown in Tables 1 and 2 . Blood pressures were slightly but not significantly higher in the hypertensive compared with the CONT group but similar in the 2 hypertensive groups (Table 1) . LV mass index, LV diameters, and diameters of the septal and posterior walls (Table 2) were significantly higher in the LVHϩ group than in the other groups. On the basis of the criteria presented in the Framingham study, [CITATION_1] all hypertensive subjects in the LVHϩ group had symmetric concentric LV hypertrophy (data not shown). Wall stress and ejection fraction were not different from each other between the groups (Table 2) . MINW, calculated per unit weight, was significantly higher in the LVHϪ group (Figure 1 ). When calculated per total LV mass, MINW was significantly higher in both hypertensive groups than in the CONT group (Figure 2) .",
